#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:7
msgid "Monero public address is what you publish to get paid."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:9
msgid ""
"An address can be generated offline and for free. It boils down to "
"generating a large random number representing your private spending key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:11
msgid ""
"Publishing your Monero address does __not__ endanger your privacy. That's "
"because in Monero transactions go to stealth addresses which are decoupled "
"from your public address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:13
msgid "There are a few **types of public addresses** in Monero:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:17
msgid ""
"Standard address - basic type of an address, also referred to as raw address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:17
msgid "Subaddress - what you should be using by default"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:17
msgid ""
"Integrated address - relevant for exchanges, merchants, and other businesses "
"accepting Monero in a fully automated way"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Standard address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:21
msgid ""
"Historically, raw address was the only available option. For that reason it "
"is the most widely adopted and supported address type."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:23
msgid ""
"Its strength is simplicity. However, these days users should prefer "
"receiving to subaddresses instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:25
msgid ""
"Technically, raw address is also a basis for creating subaddresses and "
"integrated addresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:27
msgid "Raw address is **still useful for**:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:31
msgid ""
"accepting block reward in a solo-mining scenario as other addresses are not "
"supported"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:31
msgid ""
"accepting from senders who batch payouts (like mining pools); in this "
"scenario the sender is paying multiple parties using a single transaction; "
"such transaction has multiple outputs; subaddresses do not work in this "
"scenario"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:31
msgid ""
"accepting from senders who use legacy wallets (can't send to subaddress)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:33
msgid "Monero raw address is composed of two public keys:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:36
msgid "public spend key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:36
msgid "public view key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:38
msgid ""
"It also contains a checksum and a \"network byte\" which actually identifies "
"both the network and the address type."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data structure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Index       | Size in bytes    | Description\n"
"------------|------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------\n"
"0           | 1                | identifies the network and address type; [18](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/793bc973746a10883adb2f89827e223f562b9651/src/cryptonote_config.h#L149) - main chain; [53](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/793bc973746a10883adb2f89827e223f562b9651/src/cryptonote_config.h#L161) - test chain\n"
"1           | 32               | public spend key\n"
"33          | 32               | public view key\n"
"65          | 4                | checksum ([Keccak-f[1600] hash](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/8f1f43163a221153403a46902d026e3b72f1b3e3/src/common/base58.cpp#L261) of the previous 65 bytes, trimmed to first [4](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/8f1f43163a221153403a46902d026e3b72f1b3e3/src/common/base58.cpp#L53) bytes)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:49
msgid ""
"It totals to 69 bytes. The bytes are then encoded ([src](https://github.com/"
"monero-project/monero/blob/8f1f43163a221153403a46902d026e3b72f1b3e3/src/"
"common/base58.cpp#L240)) in [Monero specific Base58](/cryptography/base58) "
"format, resulting in a 95 chars long string. Example standard address:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:51
msgid "`4AdUndXHHZ6cfufTMvppY6JwXNouMBzSkbLYfpAV5Usx3skxNgYeYTRj5UzqtReoS44qo9mtmXCqY45DJ852K5Jv2684Rge`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:53
msgid ""
"See the [source code](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/"
"f7b9f44c1b0d53170fd7f53d37fc67648f3247a2/src/cryptonote_basic/"
"cryptonote_basic_impl.cpp#L159)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generating"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generating the keys"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:59
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, a Monero address encodes two elliptic curve public keys "
"so the first step is to generate two elliptic curve private keys from which "
"the public keys may be derived."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:61
msgid ""
"Each private key is represented by a scalar between 1 and 2^252 + "
"27742317777372353535851937790883648492 inclusive. (Note: 2^252 + "
"27742317777372353535851937790883648492 + 1 is a prime order of the elliptic "
"curve basepoint, `l`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:63
msgid ""
"To generate a new private key, the convention is to generate a random 256 "
"bit numbers and reduce it modulo 2^252 + "
"27742317777372353535851937790883648493."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:65
msgid ""
"To get the public keys to be encoded in the address, the ed25519 basepoint "
"`G` is multiplied by each key scalar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checksum"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:69
msgid ""
"A checksum of the network byte and public keys is included in the address to "
"help wallet software verify that a typo hasn't been made when users enter "
"the address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:71
msgid ""
"To get this checksum, the network byte as well as the public spend and view "
"keys are concatenated together and Keccak-256 hashed. The first four bytes "
"of this hash are the checksum."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:73
msgid ""
"When wallet software parses a Monero address it should decode the address "
"and recompute the checksum and verify that it matches the checksum included "
"in the address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Base58 Encoding"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:77
msgid ""
"In an effort to further prevent errors from typos Monero addresses are "
"encoded using a special character dictionary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:79
msgid ""
"Characters used in Monero base58: "
"`123456789ABCDEFGHJKLMNPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijkmnopqrstuvwxyz`. Notice how "
"characters that look similar such as `O` and `0` are missing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:81
msgid ""
"[More about Monero base58](https://monerodocs.org/cryptography/base58/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deteministic Wallets"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:85
msgid ""
"There is no way to regulate how people choose their address keys, it is "
"simply highly suggested that they are chosen at random. The original "
"CryptoNote implementation generated each keypair randomly, independently of "
"each other. Addresses generated this way are called non-deterministic, they "
"have fallen out of popularity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:87
msgid ""
"As of present, the convention is to derive an address's view key "
"deterministically from the spend key which allows for human language encoded "
"seed mnemonics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/standard-address.md:89
msgid ""
"Deterministic addresses derive the private view key from the private spend "
"key by hashing it (conventionally Keccak-256) and reducing it modulo `l`."
msgstr ""

